&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CHARLES CLIFFORD DENTAL HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIALTY DENTIST IN ORAL SURGERY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Specialty Dentist in Oral Surgery at the Charles Clifford Dental Hospital, part of the Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. This post is permanent in tenure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an excellent opportunity for a highly motivated and enthusiastic specialist in Oral Surgery to join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers an opportunity for involvement in the undergraduate and post graduate teaching of students and trainees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have full GDC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from those unable, for personal reasons, to work on a whole time basis or a job share basis will be considered. Should any further vacancies arise shortlisted candidates may be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non-UK/EEA applicants should ensure they are aware of the recent changes to the Immigration rules. For further information on how this may affect your application visit the UK Government website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust promotes Equality of opportunity and Diversity within the workplace.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
